    • Method Detail

      • getAction

        public List<ActionType> getAction()
        Gets the value of the action property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the action property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getAction().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ActionType

      • getToggleAction

        public List<ToggleActionType> getToggleAction()
        Gets the value of the toggleAction property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the toggleAction property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getToggleAction().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ToggleActionType
